This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image denoising. The use of adaptive learning and Bayesian hyper-prior also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of computational complexity hints at the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category, while the use of pre-filtering suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
